                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><date>Sept 12 5609</date>.</p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Friend,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Yours from <placeName>Baltimore</placeName> I\n                                        duly<lb/> received but have been unable to acknowledge it\n                                        till<lb/> now. You are more fortunate than I in being able\n                                        to<lb/> run about and get a little recreation. I had fully\n                                        determined<lb/> to take a short time about the country but\n                                        L'homme proposes<lb/> et Dieu disposes. I put it off till\n                                        this week when a<lb/> child of <persName>Mr Moss</persName>\n                                        dies of cholera and I am fixed, a veritable<lb/>\n                                        <add>חשק בצוע</add>. In respect to “the mystery in\n                                        connection with a<lb/> lady in\n                                                  <placeName>Montreal</placeName>” I have to remark\n                                        (the ladies of course<lb/> claiming first attention from we\n                                        modern Rabbanim)since<lb/>\n                                        <persName>S Selig newman</persName> says in a sermon\n                                        preached at the <placeName>London</placeName><lb/> Jewish\n                                        free school, “the key <add>?</add> used formerly to be\n                                                  <add>והוא מזל זך</add><lb/> but now, complains\n                                                  <persName>newman</persName>, perhaps from\n                                        actual<lb/> experience poor fellow, “it is <add>והוא ימזל\n                                                  זך</add>”, the Lecture<lb/> meant no doubt\n                                        pathetically to say we had been <add>קל</add><lb/> enough,\n                                        and so allowed the ladies to turn &amp; <add>?</add> at\n                                        us<lb/> in the <add>נפעל</add> form.) but to <add>?</add>\n                                        from this long<lb/> parenthesis to the “mystery” Did I\n                                        mention my lady?<lb/> Certainly not and yet you seem very\n                                        anxious to assure<lb/> me that “nothing has ever passed\n                                        between us”<add>?</add> who<lb/> are us? You are one, and\n                                        who is the second—Oh<lb/> you guilty man! You can't keep a\n                                        secret too, I find.<lb/> It is certainly very kind of you to\n                                        hope the lady <sic>wont</sic><lb/> refuse a good match, even\n                                        myself, in your account after I already</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3mg7gc18/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
